  <static seed="1615" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation290.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>B</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{n} = \frac{8}{B+8} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>B = 8n-8</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{n\mathopen{}\left(B+8\right)}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{n} \amp = \frac{8}{B+8}   \\
   \frac{1}{n} \cdot n(B+8) \amp = \frac{8}{B+8} \cdot n(B+8) \\
   B+8 \amp = 8n \\
   B \amp = 8n - 8
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
